There's been an explosion at a chemical factory in New Germany, in KwaZulu-Natal. Two people have been taken to hospital with life-threatening injuries. eNCA reporter Thuba Vilane was on the scene. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - There has been an explosion at a chemical factory in Durban on Tuesday.
Two people have been taken to hospital with life-threatening injuries. READ: Seven people treated for smoke inhalation after Engen refinery fire Six others have escaped with moderate injuries. The road leading to the factory has been closed. Fire engines and rescue personnel have been dispatched to the area.